# Phosphor Icons Guidelines

## Import Strategy

Only import icons you use to reduce bundle size:

### ✅ GOOD - Selective Imports

```javascript
import { Heart, Star, User } from '@phosphor-icons/vue';
```

### ❌ BAD - Wildcard Imports

```javascript
import * as Icons from '@phosphor-icons/vue'; // Bloats bundle
```

## BaseIcon Wrapper Component

Always wrap icons in a reusable `BaseIcon.vue` component with configurable props:

```vue
<!-- components/BaseIcon.vue -->
<script setup>
import { computed } from 'vue';

const props = defineProps({
  name: {
    type: String,
    required: true,
  },
  size: {
    type: [String, Number],
    default: 24,
  },
  weight: {
    type: String,
    default: 'regular', // 'thin', 'light', 'regular', 'bold', 'fill', 'duotone'
  },
  color: {
    type: String,
    default: 'currentColor',
  },
});

const iconComponent = computed(() => {
  // Dynamically import based on name prop
  return require(`@phosphor-icons/vue`)[props.name];
});
</script>

<template>
  <component 
    :is="iconComponent" 
    :size="size" 
    :weight="weight" 
    :color="color"
  />
</template>
```

## Usage Example

```vue
<!-- YourComponent.vue -->
<script setup>
import BaseIcon from '@/components/BaseIcon.vue';
</script>

<template>
  <button class="flex items-center gap-2">
    <BaseIcon name="Heart" size={20} weight="bold" color="red" />
    Like
  </button>
</template>
```

## Anti-patterns

### ❌ BAD - Icons with Logic

```vue
<script setup>
import { Heart } from '@phosphor-icons/vue';

// DON'T: Logic in icon component
const isFilled = ref(false);
</script>

<template>
  <!-- Icon shouldn't have state -->
  <Heart :filled="isFilled" />
</template>
```

### ❌ BAD - Inconsistent Props

```vue
<!-- Avoid mixing prop names -->
<Heart size="24" weight="bold" />
<Star size="24" weight="bold" fill />
<User w="24" wt="bold" />
```

## Icon Properties

Configure only these props through `BaseIcon`:

| Property | Type | Options |
|----------|------|---------|
| `size` | String/Number | Any valid size (16, 20, 24, 32, etc.) |
| `weight` | String | 'thin', 'light', 'regular', 'bold', 'fill', 'duotone' |
| `color` | String | Any valid CSS color |

Icons are presentation-only. Move logic to parent components or composables.
